Yeah I saw that it's part of the main board on Enri's schematics now. One problem is that most games requires a certain amount of successful reads of the mic in a certain period of time for things to happen. But most microphones nowadays seems to have gone bad and are super insensitive as a result. Thus it's not strange if it doesn't work in Zelda or Kid Icarus, you might need to test it in a more sensitive testing program.<br /><br />I wonder if I could replace my mic for a new electret condenser microphone and see if it gets more sensitive.<br /><br />It would be interesting if someone would get this to work on their NES (as there actually are games that requires mic input <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.famicomworld.com/forum/index.php?topic=2355.0">http://www.famicomworld.com/forum/index ... pic=2355.0</a><!-- m -->). Though for my own sake, as a Famicom user, I would like to add the missing START and SELECT for controller II. At least the non-Japanese versions of Battletoads requires it for two player mode.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6013">Pokun</a> — Sat Jul 12, 2014 4:57 pm</p><hr />
